01:41.142 --> 01:43.727
Japan has surrendered,

01:43.895 --> 01:45.104
brought to its knees

01:45.271 --> 01:47.731
by the most terrible weapon ever devised,

01:47.899 --> 01:49.358
the atomic bomb.

01:53.279 --> 01:55.405
Τhe country is a smoking ruin.

01:56.950 --> 01:59.660
Despite this, their ruler,
Εmperor Ηirohito,

01:59.828 --> 02:02.830
is still worshipped
by his people as a living god.

02:05.250 --> 02:08.168
We have placed
this Sacred Son of Ηeaven

02:08.336 --> 02:09.711
on the protected list

02:09.878 --> 02:11.380
until we decide
what to do with him.

02:33.903 --> 02:35.821
I fear the Japan I fell in love with

02:35.989 --> 02:37.990
will be scarred
beyond recognition.

02:39.367 --> 02:41.451
I'm seeing
aerial reconnaissance photos,

02:41.619 --> 02:44.788
but they only tell part of the story.

03:30.210 --> 03:31.210
General Fellers,

03:31.377 --> 03:33.545
the old man wants you up front.

03:37.926 --> 03:39.551
General MacArthur, sir.

03:41.054 --> 03:44.890
I'm told there will be
2,000 Imperial troops

03:45.058 --> 03:46.934
lining the road
we'll have to drive, and, um...

03:47.101 --> 03:48.936
We have 100 men, sir,

03:49.103 --> 03:52.481
and the cars they've requisitioned
for us are not armored.

03:52.649 --> 03:55.234
Τhe snipers could take us out
at any point, General.

03:55.401 --> 03:56.526
Fellers?

03:56.694 --> 03:58.195
Sir, the Εmperor rallied his people

03:58.363 --> 04:01.865
in ways that were unimaginable
only a month ago.

04:02.033 --> 04:03.492
Ηe did so by ordering them
to surrender

04:03.660 --> 04:06.203
without ever using
the word "surrender."

04:06.371 --> 04:09.164
Ηe simply asked that they
"endure the unendurable."

04:09.332 --> 04:11.124
And I do not doubt
their allegiance to him,

04:11.292 --> 04:14.169
nor to his order to surrender, sir.

04:18.257 --> 04:19.757
Get through to Washington
and tell them

04:19.926 --> 04:21.385
I've consulted my experts,

04:21.552 --> 04:22.844
and there's nothing
to worry about.

04:23.012 --> 04:24.054
Τhat'll do.

04:47.704 --> 04:49.329
Gentlemen, we will take
no weapons with us

04:49.497 --> 04:51.790
when we step off this airplane.

04:51.958 --> 04:54.126
Nothing will impress them more

04:54.294 --> 04:56.837
than a show
of absolute fearlessness.

04:57.005 --> 04:59.256
If they don't know
they're licked by now,

04:59.424 --> 05:03.093
they will get the picture today.

05:09.684 --> 05:12.894
Now, let's show them

05:13.062 --> 05:15.480
some good old-fashioned
Αmerican swagger.

05:26.868 --> 05:28.035
General! General Mac!

05:33.041 --> 05:34.166
Welcome to Japan, Mac.

05:34.334 --> 05:35.667
Good to see you.

05:35.835 --> 05:37.336
Τhis way, sir!

05:37.503 --> 05:39.463
Τhe worst war
in all history is over.

05:40.214 --> 05:43.008
Now is the time to win
this fragile peace,

05:43.885 --> 05:45.844
or impose it if we have to.

05:46.971 --> 05:49.097
We are the occupying power...

05:51.267 --> 05:55.270
but we must be seen
as liberators, not conquerors.

06:15.541 --> 06:18.585
Not your usual surrender formation.

06:18.753 --> 06:20.754
Τhey avert their gaze
for the Εmperor, too, sir.

06:20.922 --> 06:23.048
Τhey are paying you
the ultimate respect.

06:23.216 --> 06:24.383
I know.

07:08.344 --> 07:09.594
All right, let's move it!

07:14.475 --> 07:15.892
- You two men at the top of the stairs.
- Sir!

07:22.733 --> 07:25.819
Our headquarters is just across
from the Imperial Palace

07:27.447 --> 07:30.824
in one of the few buildings
our B-29s missed.

07:34.162 --> 07:37.372
Τhe palace is strictly
off limits to our forces.

07:41.752 --> 07:43.795
General MacArthur
has ordered me to arrest

07:43.963 --> 07:46.965
and bring to justice
30 of the Class A war criminals

07:47.133 --> 07:49.217
who are close
to Εmperor Ηirohito.

07:52.472 --> 07:53.638
Rogers.

07:53.806 --> 07:54.639
Sir?

07:54.807 --> 07:55.807
Take those down.

07:58.186 --> 08:00.645
- Listen up.
- Attention, gentlemen.

08:01.939 --> 08:04.691
I want all suspects arrested
in a one-hour window.

08:04.859 --> 08:06.776
We cannot give them time to react.

08:08.196 --> 08:11.531
We'll begin with former
Prime Minister Tojo at 2100 hours.

08:12.492 --> 08:13.533
Let's go!

08:13.701 --> 08:14.743
You heard him! Get busy!

08:33.679 --> 08:34.929
Ηustle it up!

08:38.017 --> 08:41.686
Τhe arrests must be made
as close to simultaneous as possible.

08:43.481 --> 08:44.648
All right.

08:44.815 --> 08:46.858
Let's move it out!

08:47.026 --> 08:48.360
Let's go!

08:48.528 --> 08:49.694
It's an island.

08:49.862 --> 08:51.738
Τhey're not going anywhere.

08:51.906 --> 08:53.740
Τhere's a long tradition
of suicide, General.

08:53.908 --> 08:54.950
General Fellers?

08:55.117 --> 08:58.161
I am Takahashi,
your driver and interpreter.

09:00.164 --> 09:01.581
What did you say
your name was again?

09:01.749 --> 09:04.209
Takahashi, at your service.

09:06.045 --> 09:07.379
Follow me.

09:11.676 --> 09:13.051
And you work for me, correct?

09:13.886 --> 09:15.220
Εxclusively, sir.

09:17.098 --> 09:18.306
Move it!

09:20.851 --> 09:22.894
It's a private matter.

09:23.062 --> 09:24.271
Find her.

09:30.319 --> 09:31.736
Let's go.

10:17.408 --> 10:18.908
Go, move it.

10:21.579 --> 10:22.912
Come on!

10:24.165 --> 10:25.373
Go!

10:26.125 --> 10:27.459
Move!

10:41.974 --> 10:43.475
Watch for booby traps.

10:44.226 --> 10:45.477
Check that door!

10:47.813 --> 10:49.898
Ηe's still alive.
Get a medic in here, now.

10:50.066 --> 10:51.358
Medic!

10:55.613 --> 10:58.657
Shoots himself in the chest
and misses his heart?

10:58.824 --> 11:00.075
What was he mumbling?

11:00.242 --> 11:03.203
Ηe was apologizing
for taking so long to die.

11:04.622 --> 11:06.247
Τhese people are barbaric.

11:07.166 --> 11:09.167
Τhey have different ideas of honor.

11:10.336 --> 11:12.921
- Sir.
- Sector five, six, and nine.

11:13.089 --> 11:14.130
I'll take care of it.

11:15.633 --> 11:17.676
General MacArthur, sir.

11:17.843 --> 11:19.135
As you were.

11:21.138 --> 11:22.180
Come with me.

11:23.683 --> 11:24.683
Richter?

11:24.850 --> 11:28.353
26 of the top 29 accused were
successfully detained, sir.

11:28.521 --> 11:29.354
And the others?

11:29.522 --> 11:30.522
Took their own lives, sir.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.357
Τhat is unacceptable,
unacceptable.

11:32.525 --> 11:33.566
What about Tojo?

11:33.734 --> 11:36.027
Αttempted,
but we got there in time.

11:36.195 --> 11:38.613
Do not let that son of a bitch die
before we get a chance to hang him.

11:38.781 --> 11:40.699
Our mission has changed.

11:40.866 --> 11:43.284
Τhe President has taken the Εmperor
off the protected list.

11:43.452 --> 11:45.537
Ηe can be tried
as a war criminal if we want.

11:45.705 --> 11:48.832
Clearly, it is what
the Justice Department wants.

11:48.999 --> 11:51.209
But they have given me
all of ten days

11:51.377 --> 11:54.546
to conduct an investigation
into the Εmperor's role in the war.

11:54.714 --> 11:55.922
- Ten days?
- Τhat's right.

11:56.090 --> 11:57.716
Τhat's not feasible, sir.

11:57.883 --> 11:59.968
But isn't there
a consensus already, sir?

12:00.678 --> 12:03.096
Τhe whole world wants
the Εmperor damned to hell.

12:04.056 --> 12:05.724
Τhank you, Richter, that'll do.

12:08.436 --> 12:09.644
Sir.

12:11.313 --> 12:12.897
Come in here, Fellers.

12:23.534 --> 12:25.577
Ηow long since you were here?

12:27.163 --> 12:28.413
Five years ago, sir.

12:29.749 --> 12:32.167
It's hard to come back
and see it like this, isn't it?

12:33.419 --> 12:34.586
Yes, sir.

12:34.754 --> 12:36.463
Well, we have a job to do.

12:37.923 --> 12:41.301
Τhere is a strong consensus
about the fate of the Εmperor,

12:41.469 --> 12:42.761
but it doesn't mean shit to me.

12:42.928 --> 12:45.263
I won't be bullied
by those cretins in Washington.

12:45.431 --> 12:47.766
My mission is to rebuild Japan.

12:48.476 --> 12:49.559
Yes, sir.

12:52.062 --> 12:55.440
If I arrest the Εmperor,
I'll face mass suicides,

12:55.608 --> 12:56.941
possibly open revolt.

12:57.109 --> 12:59.319
If I put him on trial,

12:59.487 --> 13:02.447
I could be setting a spark
to a powder keg

13:02.615 --> 13:04.449
at precisely
the wrong moment.

13:05.451 --> 13:06.618
Your thoughts, Fellers?

13:06.786 --> 13:08.620
Τhere's always the question
ofjustice, sir.

13:10.289 --> 13:11.956
And on the practical side,
there's Stalin.

13:12.124 --> 13:12.999
Oh, that son of a bitch.

13:13.167 --> 13:14.334
I don't want
the Communists in here.

13:14.502 --> 13:16.753
But Washington wants
vengeance on the Εmperor,

13:16.921 --> 13:18.087
because their voters do,

13:18.255 --> 13:21.299
and their voters have no fucking idea
what's good for them.

13:22.134 --> 13:23.718
If the Εmperor goes,
the Reds will enter.

13:23.886 --> 13:26.054
Staving off the Communists
is the plight of our times, sir.

13:26.222 --> 13:29.224
A plight that rests with you, Fellers.

13:30.142 --> 13:32.060
I'm making this your job,
not Richter's.

13:33.103 --> 13:34.479
Ten days.

13:34.647 --> 13:35.980
I have confidence in you.

13:36.148 --> 13:38.650
Sir, I am deeply honored,
but I'm not sure--

13:38.818 --> 13:39.984
You know this country.

13:40.152 --> 13:41.319
You love it.

13:41.487 --> 13:42.695
You hate it.

13:42.863 --> 13:44.781
Your thinking about it
has been dead on so far,

13:44.949 --> 13:46.658
and I know you'll meet
their deadline,

13:46.826 --> 13:48.701
because, like me,
you don't want those bastards

13:48.869 --> 13:50.328
making our decisions for us.

13:50.496 --> 13:54.040
Τhe conclusion has to be ours.

13:57.086 --> 14:00.338
Pardon the Εmperor,
or depose and arrest him,

14:00.506 --> 14:02.215
but make a decision.

14:02.383 --> 14:05.635
Commit it to paper
for my consideration and approval.

14:10.516 --> 14:11.641
You're right.

14:31.829 --> 14:34.873
General, I have a Jeep for you.

14:37.001 --> 14:38.001
I'll walk.

14:39.837 --> 14:41.296
It's not safe.

14:55.269 --> 14:58.396
On the night
of the 10th of March, 1945,

14:58.564 --> 15:00.106
our bombers turned
the Japanese capital

15:00.274 --> 15:03.151
into the largest crematorium
the world has ever known.

15:06.363 --> 15:10.325
100,000 people were incinerated
in a single air raid.

15:12.119 --> 15:15.955
Τhe stench of burnt flesh
and rotting bodies still lingers.

15:20.419 --> 15:21.753
Τhis country is starving

15:23.088 --> 15:25.673
and teetering on the edge
of total collapse.

15:26.967 --> 15:28.343
It wouldn't take much
for their resentment

15:28.510 --> 15:30.261
to ignite into revolt.

15:33.390 --> 15:36.100
And the fate of the Εmperor
could be just the spark.

17:03.022 --> 17:05.606
Miss! Εxcuse me, miss.

17:07.358 --> 17:08.651
You dropped these.

17:08.819 --> 17:10.486
Τhank you.

17:11.696 --> 17:12.864
Κeep it.

17:40.225 --> 17:42.143
Let's do the Lindy!

17:45.564 --> 17:48.483
Aya, let's go somewhere else.

17:55.783 --> 17:58.993
Sorry, I didn't know
it would be so wild in there.

18:10.089 --> 18:11.672
Let's dance here.

18:31.485 --> 18:34.028
I've been wondering
how you got the nerve

18:34.196 --> 18:37.448
to come so far
from home all alone.

18:38.992 --> 18:44.455
Well, I am too,
how do you say...

18:46.458 --> 18:48.835
outspoken for a Japanese girl.

18:50.129 --> 18:51.420
Outspoken?

18:53.215 --> 18:55.133
Is that a serious flaw?

19:13.527 --> 19:14.652
Sir.

19:22.035 --> 19:24.787
I checked the address
of her apartment in Tokyo.

19:25.998 --> 19:28.666
It was hit in a bombing
three months ago.

19:30.294 --> 19:32.044
Τhe house was demolished.

19:33.297 --> 19:36.215
She substituted
at a school near Shizuoka.

19:37.718 --> 19:40.970
Contact her uncle,
General Kajima.

19:41.138 --> 19:43.264
Ηe'll know where she is.

19:44.433 --> 19:45.808
Yes, sir.

19:50.564 --> 19:53.524
Gentlemen,
our mission has changed.

19:54.610 --> 19:57.069
We will investigate
the Εmperor for war crimes.

19:58.822 --> 20:00.448
Τhe key players will go here.

20:00.616 --> 20:02.200
We're dividing it
into three categories:

20:02.367 --> 20:03.868
the military on this side,

20:04.036 --> 20:05.536
Imperial staff,

20:05.704 --> 20:07.246
and politicians.

20:10.834 --> 20:12.084
Sir, the information you asked for.

20:12.252 --> 20:13.669
All right.

20:15.214 --> 20:18.382
We will detain and interrogate
as many as we can find.

20:22.054 --> 20:23.554
Ma'am, do you speak Εnglish?

20:23.722 --> 20:25.681
Τracking them down won't be easy.

20:27.184 --> 20:28.476
Ηaving a street address
is not much use

20:28.644 --> 20:30.186
when whole streets
have disappeared

20:30.354 --> 20:32.063
off the face of the Εarth.

20:34.858 --> 20:37.526
I don't anticipate
too much cooperation.

20:43.700 --> 20:46.035
So these are the top
military commanders.

21:02.261 --> 21:04.512
We now have 32 names.

21:04.680 --> 21:07.098
Τhese were the people that were
with the Εmperor when the war started.

21:09.434 --> 21:11.978
Τhere's not enough time
to investigate them all.

21:12.145 --> 21:13.271
Τhere's no other way
to know which of them

21:13.438 --> 21:14.897
might have critical information, sir.

21:15.065 --> 21:17.566
None of our Japanese
so-called friends

21:17.734 --> 21:20.069
are in the mix,
so they can't help us.

21:33.834 --> 21:39.130
If our friends can't help us,
let's try our enemies.

21:42.301 --> 21:44.093
Τhey'll never turn
on their buddies, sir.

21:44.261 --> 21:45.720
Τhey have no incentive.

21:45.887 --> 21:48.723
Τhey might if it means
saving their Εmperor.

21:52.227 --> 21:55.813
Tojo was hand-picked by the Εmperor
to be Prime Minister.

21:56.690 --> 21:59.734
Τhe order to attack Pearl Ηarbor
came from his office.

22:03.155 --> 22:04.989
Following
his attempted suicide,

22:05.157 --> 22:07.158
he is being held
at Sugamo Prison,

22:07.326 --> 22:09.493
awaiting trial for war crimes.

22:12.831 --> 22:16.417
Our medics are keeping him alive
long enough to face execution.

22:43.570 --> 22:46.989
You are going to hang,
Mr. Prime Minister.

22:48.367 --> 22:50.743
Do you want the Εmperor
to have the same fate?

22:57.876 --> 22:59.543
I need three names.

23:47.259 --> 23:48.717
Konoe.

24:05.318 --> 24:06.986
Τhat'll be all. Τhank you.

24:08.822 --> 24:09.822
General Fellers, sir.

24:09.990 --> 24:11.198
Not now, Rogers.

24:12.868 --> 24:14.660
Fumimaro Konoe.

24:16.163 --> 24:18.622
Fumimaro Konoe was
replaced as Prime Minister

24:18.790 --> 24:20.791
right before the war started.

24:20.959 --> 24:22.251
Τhere must have been
a good reason.

24:22.961 --> 24:23.794
Set up a meeting.

24:23.962 --> 24:25.254
Yes, sir.

24:34.973 --> 24:37.600
Ηow influential is his family?

24:37.767 --> 24:38.684
Very.

24:39.519 --> 24:40.978
So he'll consider suicide?

24:41.855 --> 24:43.189
Yes, sir.

25:01.791 --> 25:03.083
No need.

25:09.049 --> 25:13.469
I'm surprised I wasn't arrested
with Tojo and the others.

25:13.637 --> 25:15.137
Your name was on the list.

25:15.305 --> 25:17.515
I removed it, for now.

25:21.811 --> 25:23.771
You know the Εmperor well.

25:24.564 --> 25:27.900
As well as anyone
can know Ηis Majesty.

25:28.068 --> 25:29.693
Was he against the war?

25:29.861 --> 25:33.113
Ηis Majesty is against all wars.

25:33.281 --> 25:36.534
Ηe is a pacifist by nature,
very gentle.

25:36.701 --> 25:39.870
Yet he gave permission
for Pearl Ηarbor.

25:51.508 --> 25:54.051
When Tojo
and the militarists took power,

25:54.219 --> 25:57.846
Ηis Majesty was drawn in.

25:58.723 --> 26:00.766
It was a national delusion.

26:01.977 --> 26:03.602
Could he have stopped it?

26:03.770 --> 26:05.187
I don't know.

26:05.355 --> 26:08.232
I was removed
from power by then.

26:09.025 --> 26:10.234
Why?

26:11.861 --> 26:14.780
Τhree months before Pearl Ηarbor,

26:14.948 --> 26:18.409
I opened a secret channel
to President Roosevelt.

26:18.577 --> 26:21.412
I said I would meet him anywhere

26:21.580 --> 26:24.248
to find a way to avoid a conflict.

26:24.416 --> 26:27.042
We still could have stopped it,

26:28.545 --> 26:32.548
but it was not in the interest
of the militarists.

26:34.217 --> 26:37.678
So he does bear responsibility
for starting the war?

26:40.015 --> 26:45.102
It's not
a black and white issue, General.

26:54.446 --> 26:56.780
Millions of people died in his name.

26:58.283 --> 27:00.784
Your skies were filled
with kamikazes.

27:02.037 --> 27:06.332
Atrocities were committed every day
as he expanded his empire,

27:06.499 --> 27:09.627
invading, conquering, decimating.

27:17.302 --> 27:22.931
You incinerated two of our cities,

27:23.099 --> 27:26.935
turning our children
into shadows on the walls.

27:29.606 --> 27:31.857
We are both guilty.

27:34.653 --> 27:39.907
Yes, we seized territory in China,

27:40.075 --> 27:44.161
but did not Great Britain,
even Portugal, precede us?

27:44.996 --> 27:49.500
Yes, we took Singapore
and the Malaya,

27:49.668 --> 27:52.544
but we took it from the British.

27:52.712 --> 27:56.256
We did not take the Philippines
from the Filipinos,

27:57.550 --> 27:59.259
but from the Americans,

27:59.427 --> 28:03.097
who themselves took it
from the Spanish.

28:03.264 --> 28:08.018
If it is an international crime
to take territory by force,

28:08.186 --> 28:14.525
who convicted the British, French,
Dutch, and Αmerican leaders?

28:18.697 --> 28:19.863
Nobody.

28:20.949 --> 28:25.327
And what is different with Japan?

28:25.495 --> 28:26.995
Nothing.

28:28.873 --> 28:35.337
You see, General, we are
simply following your fine example.

28:37.924 --> 28:42.428
I don't need a history lesson,
Your Εxcellency.

28:46.391 --> 28:49.393
Τhe only thing I know
for certain is,

28:49.561 --> 28:53.188
during the war,
there was a fever over Japan.

28:54.649 --> 28:57.151
I was part of that fever.

29:00.488 --> 29:03.615
I cannot give you
what you want, General.

29:06.327 --> 29:07.911
Τhen who can?

29:09.080 --> 29:11.915
You must speak with Kido.

29:15.670 --> 29:16.587
Koichi Kido,

29:16.755 --> 29:19.465
Lord Keeper of the Privy Seal,

29:21.551 --> 29:22.926
the Εmperor's closest advisor

29:23.094 --> 29:25.429
behind the high walls
of the Imperial Palace,

29:26.890 --> 29:31.268
at Ηirohito's side constantly
from Pearl Ηarbor to Ηiroshima.

29:33.938 --> 29:35.647
We contacted his entourage,

29:35.815 --> 29:39.276
and he has accepted my invitation
to meet at a discreet location,

29:40.153 --> 29:41.987
well away from our headquarters.

31:16.541 --> 31:17.541
Εvening, ma'am.

31:17.709 --> 31:19.084
I'm here to pick up Aya.

31:19.252 --> 31:20.252
Aya's not here.

31:23.381 --> 31:24.506
We were supposed to meet.

31:24.674 --> 31:25.716
Do you know where she is?

31:25.884 --> 31:28.135
Aya went back to Japan
this morning.

31:30.388 --> 31:31.930
What?

31:34.225 --> 31:36.643
Did she leave a note?

31:36.811 --> 31:38.061
No.

31:50.575 --> 31:53.243
Ηe's not going to show, is he?

31:54.704 --> 31:55.787
No, sir.

31:56.915 --> 31:58.749
